  "text": "These processes are associated with abnormalities in adipocyte functioning. Obesity alters the metabolic and endocrine functions of adipose tissue and leads to increased release of hormones, fatty acids, and proinflammatory molecules that contribute to obesity-related complications [CITATION_1] . Proinflammatory mediators released from adipose tissue cannot only cause direct endothelial damage but also generate excess free radical formation. Such activities are exhibited by, for example, TNF-α (tumor necrosis factor alpha), Il-6 (interleukin 6), CRP (C-reactive protein), leptin, and resistin [CITATION_2] .",
